<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-09-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-09-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="234" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d234">
                    <head>No. 234.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Denby</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-09-05"><hi rend="italic">September</hi> 5,
                            1888</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Bayard</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington:</hi></p>
                    <p>Believe treaty has been rejected. Have demanded from foreign office positive
                        information some days since. No information has yet been received.</p>
                    <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Denby.</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>